text:
In my opinion, BEST canteen in NTU. Caifan, Japanese, Szechuan stalls are all delicious and worth the price. I highly recommend the following:
1. Laziji at Szechuan stall
2. Karaage curry rice at Japanese stall
3. Fish or sweet sour pork at Caifan stall
4. Fried dumplings at Chinese noodle stall

Rude uncle at Chinese noodle shop. Acted very defensive when confronted about cockroach leg in their dumpling noodle ðŸ¥´ whole place had a lot houseflies too. Drink stall also put a lot of ice in your drink, totally not worth.

One of the best canteen in all campus! The Japanese stall is the best one! The service is amazing and the variety of food so good! Also the Breakfast counter is really good! The coffee and food is good! And the woman on counter is really seeet! Good prices!
Dark and gloomy atmosphere, seems depressing. Kaya toast Kaya tasted weird. Cai peng was great but expensive. Reccomend the fried chicken there. Egg from the coffee shop was over boiled.

Noodles stall's crispy guo tie is very good. Richly filled with minced pork, fresh chive and carrot.
Japanese dry ramen with chicken katsu is more value for money than katsu don.
